Free for use and distribtuion by anyone, just don't remove this README when distributing. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

== USING LICHEN ==

Some day I'll write a bit more on this, but here's a quick run down:

= Normal editing mode =
    - The two larger boxes at the top left are your current tiles
       - Click on them to open your tile library
       - Use A/Z to scroll your left click, S/X to scroll your right
    - The smaller boxes list your layers
        - Current layer is highlighted in green
        - Right now you can't actually click these to any effect
        - Hit tab to cycle your current layer
    - Hold space to switch to scrolling mode; click-drag to move around the map
    - Hit H to turn off the hover-highlight
    - Hit G to turn off the grid
 
= Tile library mode =
    - Left or right click tiles to set your current pencil tile
    - Hold space and click-drag to scroll the visible tiles

